The Shared Resources (Erlang) Testing tool is a set of utilities
written in the Erlang for testing shared resources.

The model checker has been written by Lars-Åke Fredlund
(Facultad de Informática, Universidad Politécnica de Madrid, Spain) 
with contributions by Raúl Alborodo (IMDEA software).

Prerequisites:
- To use the testing tool the Quviq QuickCheck testing tool is required
(see http://www.quviq.com)
- To check shared resources coded in Java we recommend the use
of the JavaErlang library
(https://github.com/fredlund/JavaErlang)

For more information please consult the documentation in:

- The source code repository at
  https://bitbucket.org/fredlund1/shared_resources_erlang
- Information about shared resources:
  http://babel.ls.fi.upm.es/~rnnalborodo/sr_web/


